    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/moore-speaks-bsg-backstory-and-fracks-it#comment-6666" class="active">Not impossible, but...</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Sun, 2009-01-18 20:23.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Damned unlikely.   For the 12 tribes to decide to name themselves after the Zodiac of Earth, you need a lot more than a colonist coming back and telling a story.   Tribe names and flags would only come from a deep foundation.</p>

<p>You need Kobolian culture to fall, and be replaced by culture from Earth, for the 12 tribes to take their names and symbols from the Earth sky.  It&#8217;s possible for that to happen, but you need nothing less than this.</p>

<p>So now the plot has to be:</p>

<ul>
<li>13th tribe of Cylons goes to Kobol</li>
<li>Kobol civilization is destroyed</li>
<li>Earth cylons come back to Kobol and take over</li>
<li>12 tribes form, taking names and flags from Earth</li>
<li>New Lords of Kobol tell tribes to beat it.</li>
<li>Earth is nuked</li>
<li>Kobol is destroyed again.</li>
</ul>

<p>Gets messy.</p>
</div>
