  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/moore-speaks-bsg-backstory-and-fracks-it#comment-6685" class="active">Oh please</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by misterd (not verified) on Mon, 2009-01-19 09:00.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>Realistic SF is not the same as Hard SF. We started out with hyperdrives, artificial gravity, visions, and ressurecting robots indistinguishable from humans on even a molecular level. The show was never going for hard SF. It is hard*er* than shows like Trek, but still far from hard, let alone "real" science. I suspect RDM was emphasizing the "fiction" part of real, with characters and human stories far more "real" than what we'd seen in SF television to this point.</p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links"><li class="first last comment_reply"><a href="/comment/reply/861/6685" class="comment_reply">reply</a></li>
</ul></div>
