<div class="indented"><a id="comment-6696"></a>
  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/battlestar/moore-speaks-bsg-backstory-and-fracks-it#comment-6696" class="active">I don&#039;t disagree</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Mon, 2009-01-19 14:22.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>But again, there are a few ways to look at &#8220;hard&#8221; SF.     I made a joke when people say that hard SF obeys the laws of physics.  I say &#8220;Yes, but so do Harlequin Romances.&#8221;   There is more to it.</p>

<p>It is also good for all fiction, not just SF, to obey the rules of logic.   If you show that the 12 tribes have the star patterns of the Earth Zodiac on their flags, there has to be a logical path by which that happened.   That has nothing to do with the science part of things.</p>
</div>
